1604552400.title: Bargain Hunt
1604552400.descr: Anita Manning presents today's Bargain Hunt from the Elsecar Heritage Centre in North Yorkshire, which is home to the World's oldest steam engine, the Newcomen Beam Engine. Experts Kate Bliss and Jonathan Pratt are helping the reds and blues to find a Bargain that will hopefully make a profit at auction in Knutsford with auctioneer Nick Hall.

1604555100.title: Bargain Hunt
1604555100.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1604557800.title: Father Brown
1604557800.descr: Father Brown is a Catholic priest and an amateur detective solving murder cases, set during the 1950s in the fictional village Kembleford in Cotswold area, England. He uses his own wits as well as skills of his close friends, and being a priest allows him to look straight to the truth. He is strongly against the capital punishment for the capital crimes, as still applied in Britain of that time.

1604560500.title: Father Brown
1604560500.descr: Mark Williams, Hetty Baynes, Carol Royle, Nicola Thorp, Sorcha Cusack, Emer Kenny. Drama series based on the novels of GK Chesterton. When a local writer is murdered, Father Brown must delve into her infamous novel Lulu and Lucia for inspiration.

1604563200.title: Impossible
1604563200.descr: Entertaining and educational British quiz show, hosted by Rick Edwards, where 24 regular contestants compete throughout the series to answer tricky questions. 1604606400.title: Ordinary Lies
1604606400.descr: Drama and deceit lurks in every corner of the shop floor and office in Ordinary Lies, with employees concealing dark secrets from their coworkers. Series one focusses on the workers at JS Motors, a car showroom, with series two focussing on Coopers Outdoors, a sports-goods store.

1604609700.title: Stella
